properties.headline: Flood Warning issued January 7 at 4:15AM PST until January 7 at 11:41PM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
...The Flood Warning continues for the following rivers in
Washington...

Stillaguamish River At Arlington affecting Snohomish County
Tolt River Above Carnation affecting King County
Snoqualmie River Near Snoqualmie Falls affecting King County

North West Region
Central West Region

Another 2 to 4 inches of precipitation is forecast for the central
Cascades until a cold front moves through the area this evening.
Snow levels will be as high as 5000 feet ahead of the front.
Precipation rates and snow levels will lower behind the front.

The Flood Warning continues for
The Tolt River Above Carnation
* Until this evening.
* At  3:15 AM Tuesday the flow was 5017 cfs.
* Flood flow is 5000 cfs.
* Minor flooding is occurring and Minor flooding is forecast.
* Forecast...The river will continue to rise and crest near 5826 cfs
around 10 AM Tuesday. The river will fall below flood flow
this afternoon.
* Impact...At 5000 cfs, the Tolt River will flood Tolt River Rd NE and
many driveways. Some homes in the San Souci area could be
inaccessible due to deep and quick flood waters. This river level
on the Tolt corresponds to a phase 3 flood in the King County flood
system.
properties.instruction:
Do not drive cars...vans...or trucks through flooded areas...this is
the cause of most flood related deaths in Washington. Be alert for
rapid changes and monitor developments by listening to NOAA Weather
radio or other local media.

NWSheadline: Flood Warning extended until this evening
